==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Fraternize
<hw>Fra"ter*nize</hw> <pr>(? ⟦or⟧ ?; 277)</pr>, <pos>v. i.</pos>
<vmorph>[<pos>imp. & p. p.</pos> <conjf>Fraternized</conjf>
<pr>(#)</pr>; <pos>p. pr. & vb. n.</pos>. <conjf>Fraternizing</conjf>
<pr>(#)</pr>.]</vmorph> <ety>[Cf. F. <ets>fraterniser</ets>.]</ety>
<def>To associate or hold fellowship as brothers, or as men of like
occupation or character; to have brotherly feelings.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Fraternize</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Fraternize
<hw>Fra"ter*nize</hw>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <def>To bring into fellowship or
brotherly sympathy.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Correspondence for <qex>fraternizing</qex> the two nations.</q>
<rj><qau>Burke.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

